§ Why ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Can we characterize positive (semi-)definite matrices in terms
    of their eigenvalues? ⦉
⦉

§ Main Result ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Using eigenvalue decompositions, we can answer in the
    affirmative. ⦉
⦉

<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ Suppose $A ∈ 𝗦^d$ has smallest eigenvalue $λ_{\min}(A)$. ⦉

  ‖ Then
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ \begin{aligned} ⦉

      ‖ A ∈ 𝗦_+^d \quad ＆\iff \quad λ_{\min}(A) ≥ 0 ᜶ ⦉ ‖ \quad
        ＆\iff \quad \tr AB ≥ 0 \text{ for all } B ∈ 𝗦_+^d. ⦉

      ‖ \end{aligned} ⦉
    ⦉
    and
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ \begin{aligned} ⦉

      ‖ A ∈ 𝗦_{++}^d \quad ＆\iff \quad λ_{\min}(A) > 0 ᜶ ⦉

      ‖ \quad ＆\iff \quad \tr AB > 0 \text{ for all nonzero }
        B ∈ 𝗦_{++}^d. ⦉

      ‖ \end{aligned} ⦉
    ⦉⦉
</statement>
